{"id": 225027800, "title": "Isabella Strahan Celebrates Her Birthday 6 Months Late After She Missed It During Brain Surgery", "text": "Michael Strahan's daughter Isabella Strahan is having a birthday redo while at home in between chemotherapy treatments for her brain tumor. On May 27, the 19-year-old student and model posted the latest installment of her YouTube series, where she's been sharing her health journey after having emergency surgery in October 2023 to remove a large medulloblastoma \u2014 a type of malignant tumor \u2014 in her cerebellum. In the vlog, Isabella is at her New York City home resting after undergoing her third round of chemotherapy. Alongside her friend Dallas and twin sister Sophia, she films herself baking cupcakes, hoping to re-celebrate her 19th birthday. Isabella and Sophia\u2019s birthday is October 28. However, Isabella was hospitalized at the time due to her emergency craniotomy. \u201cWe\u2019re doing a little birthday celebration because I was not conscious for my 19th birthday,\u201d she said with a laugh. \u201cSo we\u2019re doing a little birthday thing about six months later.\u201d Isabella and Sophia sang \u201cHappy Birthday\u201d to themselves and blew out the candle on their cupcakes before their dad Michael Strahan came and gave them a big hug. The PEOPLE Puzzler crossword is here! How quickly can you solve it? Play now! The vlog also included a clip from Isabella\u2019s first brain surgery in October 2023. She opened up about the moment in her very first vlog post in January. In the clip, her family and friends decorated her hospital room with balloons, flowers and birthday signs. They all sang \u201cHappy Birthday\u201d to her with a cake as she laid unconscious after surgery. The model admitted that she doesn\u2019t remember everything about her first hospitalization, relying on her family and friends to fill in the gaps about her experience. \u201cIt\u2019s super sweet to see how much people care and I think that was a big thing [for my recovery],\u201d she said at the time. Never miss a story \u2014 sign up for PEOPLE's free daily newsletter to stay up-to-date on the best of what PEOPLE has to offer, from celebrity news to compelling human interest stories. Isabella has since undergone radiation, three brain surgeries and three rounds of chemotherapy. In her May 21 vlog, she shared her excitement because she only has one more round of chemotherapy left. \u201cI just want it to be June already,\u201d she said. \u201cThat\u2019s the thing, I just wait around for the next time I get chemo and I\u2019m kind of scared once I\u2019m done, how I\u2019m gonna go back to normal life. Because I feel like there\u2019s always gonna be another treatment or something I have to do. But that\u2019s a later problem.\u201d \u201cOtherwise, I\u2019m doing good,\u201d she added. Since her diagnosis, Isabella has been documenting her health journey on YouTube to benefit Duke Children's Hospital & Health Center.", "summary": "Isabella Strahan was hospitalized for an emergency craniotomy during her 19th birthday in October", "url": "https://people.com/isabella-strahan-re-celebrates-19th-birthday-after-missing-it-during-first-brain-surgery-8654236", "image": "https://people.com/thmb/488_beTCEMx-LMABP5e9r3pm9vU=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc():focal(746x216:748x218)/isabella-strahan-052724-2-647e40cd94344520ad3a640d45f738fe.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-05-29 13:13:08", "author": "Vanessa Etienne", "authors": ["Vanessa Etienne"], "language": "en", "source_country": "US", "sentiment": 0.124}